HEADWORD: close-hauled
<hw>close-hauled</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>Under way and moving as nearly as
possible toward the direction from which the wind blows; having the
sails trimmed for sailing as close to the wind as possible; -- said of a
sailing vessel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

